# F7 Controller — local-dev environment template.
#
# Real deployments: install.sh / install.ps1 generate a strong POSTGRES_PASSWORD
# and write a .env automatically — you do NOT need this file.
#
# Local dev only: `cp .env.example .env` before `docker compose up`. The compose
# file requires POSTGRES_PASSWORD with no default (fails closed if unset, PB7),
# so this throwaway value keeps a from-scratch `docker compose` run working.

# REQUIRED — Postgres + OpenFGA datastore credential (no default in compose).
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=devpassword

# Optional — published controller image tag (defaults to :latest).
# CONTROLLER_IMAGE=ghcr.io/f7-platform/public-agent-binaries/controller:latest
